 Kevin Carr , 34 , from Woolacombe , Devon , ran more than a marathon a day every day for almost two years , crossing 26 countries and getting through 16 pairs of shoes to complete the feat .
He began his epic voyage at Haytor on Dartmoor in July 2013 and returned after 621 days , beating the previous record .
Mr Carr was also the first man to complete endurance run unsupported , he says of bears .